def: Having broad scutella on the front, and small scales on theposterior side, of the tarsus; -- said of certain birds.

To chide with vehemence; to scold; to censure violently.Spencer.Go, rate thy minions, proud, insulting boy! Shak.Conscience is a check to beginners in sin, reclaiming them from it,and rating them for it. Barrow.
Of or pertaining to Patagonia.-- n.
A colorless, crystalline, organic base, obtained fromrosaniline by reduction, and also from other sources. It formscolorless salts.
A calcareous tufa, in part crystalline, occurring on a largescale as a shore deposit about the Quaternary lake basins of Nevada.

That order of the Crinoidea which includes most of the livingand many fossil forms, having jointed arms around the margin of theoral disk; -- also called Brachiata and Articulata. See Illusts.under Comatula and Crinoidea.
